public class TextRepresentation
extends java.lang.Object
implements IHasLanguageIdentifier, java.lang.Comparable<TextRepresentation>

TextRepresentation is a class representing one textual content of diverse Uby-LMF classes, such as Definition, SenseExample or Statement.

getLanguageIdentifier

public java.lang.String getLanguageIdentifier()
Description copied from interface: IHasLanguageIdentifier
Returns the language identifier of this instance. The languages are, in general, represented as ISO 639-3 codes. The most frequently used language codes, as well as our additions for representing macrolanguages, dialects, retired languages, and not-yet-standardized languages are modeled as string constants in ELanguageIdentifier. Data category reference: http://www.isocat.org/rest/dc/279

Specified by:
getLanguageIdentifier in interface IHasLanguageIdentifier
Returns:
the language identifier of this instance or null, if no certain language identifier has been set or the language is unknown.
See Also:
ELanguageIdentifier

setLanguageIdentifier

public void setLanguageIdentifier(java.lang.String languageIdentifier)
Description copied from interface: IHasLanguageIdentifier
Set the given language identifier for this object. In most cases, choosing one of the string constants in ELanguageIdentifier should be sufficient. However, it is possible to use other language identifiers that are not yet modeled as constants. Use valid ISO 639-3 codes in these cases or extend the set of constant types. Data category reference: http://www.isocat.org/rest/dc/279

Specified by:
setLanguageIdentifier in interface IHasLanguageIdentifier
Parameters:
languageIdentifier - language identifier to be set.

getOrthographyName

public java.lang.String getOrthographyName()
Returns the name of the orthography used in this TextRepresentation.

For instance, an orthographe name can be "arabic" or "arabic unpointed".

Returns:
the name of the orthography used in the written text of this text representation or null, if the name of orthography is not set

getWrittenText

public java.lang.String getWrittenText()
Returns the series of sentences expressed in natural language contained in this TextRepresentation.

Returns:
the series of sentences expressed in natural language contained in this text representation or null, if this text representation does not have any written text set

Note that written text is the essential part of a text representation and should always be set under normal circumstances.
